## Your Task: Sprint 2.1 — Schema Foundations

Pure schema and prompt work. No new infrastructure, no new services — safe, contained, and unblocks everything after it.

### 1. New node types
Add to `flowos/packages/types/src/flow.types.ts`:
- **`DELETE`** (A1) — closes the CRUD set alongside existing `SELECT`/`UPDATE`.
- **`CREATE`** (A1) — insert operation, also missing today.
- **`SOURCE`** (A1) — binds the flow to a connector explicitly, as an entry node (replaces inferring the start node from in-degree).
- **`ASSIGN`** (B1) — sets in-memory execution-context variables (distinct from `UPDATE`, which persists to a connector — these were conflated before).

Exact config shapes, inputs/outputs pattern, and worked examples for every one of these: **[Architecture/node-reference.md](../Architecture/node-reference.md)** — this is the spec, match it exactly, don't improvise shapes.

### 2. Redesign `CONDITION`
Currently binary (`{ expression, trueLabel, falseLabel }`). Redesign to multi-outcome, matching CRM Decision element: one node, multiple named outcomes each with its own condition set, evaluated in order, with a default/catch-all. Exact target shape is in `node-reference.md` under `CONDITION`. Binary if/else becomes just the 2-outcome case — no separate node type.

### 3. New `U1` layer
Add a fourth layer alongside `A1`/`B1`/`D1` — kept separate deliberately, see `node-reference.md`'s intro for why. Add `DISPLAY` and `COMPONENT` node types under it. **Schema only this sprint** — they're not functional until Sprint 3/4, just need to exist in the type union and the LLM prompt so later sprints aren't blocked on a schema change.

### 4. Update the LLM generation prompt
`flowos/apps/api/src/llm/generate-flow.prompt.ts` — add the new node types, their config shapes, and the layer rule for `U1`. Keep the existing ordering rule (A1 → B1 → D1) and extend it to include `U1` where relevant (UI nodes typically come after the logic/rules that feed them).

### 5. Update everything downstream that assumes the old shapes
Grep for `CONDITION` usage in `flowos/apps/api/src/execution/` (currently mock, but the topological sort and any type references need to compile against the new shape) and `flowos/apps/web/src/components/` (canvas rendering, config panel).

