## Acceptance Criteria
- `pnpm --filter api build` and `pnpm --filter web build` both pass clean with the new types.
- Generating a flow via `/flows/generate` that needs a multi-way branch produces one `CONDITION` node with multiple labeled outcome edges, not a chain of binary conditions.
- Generating a flow that needs to accumulate a value across iterations produces an `ASSIGN` node, not a misused `UPDATE`.
- Existing Sprint 1 flows (binary-condition ones, if any were saved) don't crash the canvas — either migrate them or confirm the new shape is backward-compatible enough to render.

